The paper deals with the problem of resource allocation in 5G cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization and scheduling algorithms, which are related to information theory and systems and control theory, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. The paper proposes a neural network-based approach to solve the resource allocation problem, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper uses simulation results to evaluate the proposed approach, which involves statistical analysis and data visualization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category.
